<h4 id="monero-gui-wallet">Monero GUI Wallet</h4>

<p>You can download the beta release of Monero GUI wallet <a href="https://getmonero.org/2016/12/22/monero-core-gui-beta-released.html">here</a>.</p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-1.png" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)"><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-1.png" alt="How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-2.png" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)"><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-2.png" alt="How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p><em>Image: Allowing an app from outside of the App Store in system preferences is as much challenge as youâ€™ll be facing with the XMR GUI wallet</em></p>

<p>The GUI is much easier to work with, especially if you have worked with BTC wallets like Electrum before. You simply download your distribution from the link above, extract the file and if youâ€™re on Mac, move the app into Applications. Once you launch the GUI it guides you through the wallet creation and starts synchronizing the blockchain automatically.</p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-3.png" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)"><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-3.png" alt="How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p>If youâ€™re just creating a new wallet go with the default localhost:18081 and write down your seed and password on paper. Your wallet files will be in home/Monero/wallets.</p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-4.png" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)"><figure class="border"><amp-img itemprop="image" src="https://www.altcointrading.net/img/xmr/monero-gui-4.png" alt="How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" title="AltcoinTrading.NET - How to setup Monero core wallet (for dummies)" layout="responsive" width="700px" height="360px"></amp-img></figure></a></p>

<p>With a wallet at the ready you get into this view which is the actual GUI client. The wallet will start downloading the blockchain by itself. All you do from here is wait, and wait, and wait.</p>

